The paper deals with knowledge representation, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of category theory and logic also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of relational ologs, which are a type of knowledge representation system, and this could place the paper in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the type system and instance data, which are concepts related to databases, and this could place the paper in the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the graphical syntax of relational ologs, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category, as this sub-category deals with the analysis of algorithms and data structures.
